
[1]heritage

   HER'ITAGE, n.

   1. Inheritance; an estate that passes from an ancestor to an heir by
   descent or course of law; that which is inherited. In Scot's law, it
   sometimes signifies immovable estate, in distinction from movable.

   2. In Scripture, the saints or people of God are called his heritage,
   as being claimed by him, and the objects of his special care. 1 Pet.5.
